On this pod, I talk to legendary online cartoon man KC Green about the shifting winds of fortune when it comes to hocking your illustrated wares on the world wide web. We get into influences, webcomic history, and the ethics of merchandising.

Getting some push back to this which is fine. This is what happens when you make large sweeping statements about groups you don't belong to. Either way, I like the furries. They are the most ardent and passionate supporters of the art of cartooning in general.

I think I have an outsider's obsession with furries just because I am enamoured with the idea of people finding unusual but concrete means of mitigating the unbearable tragedy of life. Like, you have placated your existential loneliness with a dog costume. That's wonderful.
